      <h2>Construction &amp; Remodeling in Kihei</h2>
      <p>Kihei is one of the fastest-growing communities on Maui — and one of the most active construction markets on the island. The stretch of condominiums and residential neighborhoods running from the Piilani Highway corridor down to South Kihei Road has seen consistent development and renovation activity for decades, and that pace has accelerated as Maui's housing market has tightened and vacation rental investment has intensified.</p>

      <p>Great General LLC has worked extensively in Kihei. We understand the unique mix of property types here — the older condominium complexes along the waterfront, the mid-density residential neighborhoods further inland, and the newer developments along the Piilani Highway corridor. We know how to navigate HOA requirements for condo renovation work, understand the coastal exposure conditions that affect material selection, and manage the logistics of construction in a densely built community.</p>

      <p>Whether you're a homeowner planning a kitchen remodel, a vacation rental investor refreshing a unit at Kamaole Sands or Maui Banyan, or a property manager coordinating renovations across a condo complex, we bring the same level of attention and accountability to your project.</p>

      <h2>Kihei's Condo and Vacation Rental Market</h2>
      <p>Kihei's built environment is defined by its condominium communities. From the iconic waterfront complexes along the South Kihei Road oceanfront — Kamaole Beach Royale, Kamaole Sands, Mana Kai, Sugar Beach Resort, and dozens of others — to the sprawling mixed-use developments along Azeka and Piilani, condominiums represent the majority of renovation work we do in this area.</p>

      <p>Condo renovation work in Kihei has specific requirements that differ from single-family home projects:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>HOA approvals and coordination</strong> — most Kihei condo associations require pre-approval for interior renovation work, noise and hours restrictions, and often require licensed contractors specifically. We work with HOA management regularly and know how to navigate the approval process efficiently.</li>
        <li><strong>Elevator and common area logistics</strong> — material staging and debris removal in multi-story buildings requires planning. We've done enough condo work in Kihei to handle this without disrupting other residents.</li>
        <li><strong>Vacation rental turnover timing</strong> — many Kihei condo owners run active short-term rental programs, which means renovation windows are often compressed to gaps in the booking calendar. We work with owners to schedule projects around their rental income and minimize vacancy days.</li>
        <li><strong>Salt-air material specifications</strong> — oceanfront properties in Kihei have significant salt-air exposure, especially below the second floor and on ocean-facing lanais. We specify materials — particularly for metalwork, hardware, and exterior finishes — that account for this exposure level.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>South Kihei Road Corridor</h2>
      <p>The South Kihei Road corridor, running roughly from Kalepolepo Park through the Kamaole Beach parks to Keawakapu, is Kihei's most valuable real estate zone. Properties here — from oceanfront condominiums to single-family homes with beach access — command premium prices and require renovation quality to match. We've worked in this corridor and understand both the opportunity and the elevated standards that these properties require.</p>

      <p>Interior renovations in this zone often involve kitchens and bathrooms designed to appeal to high-end vacation rental guests, durable flooring that can handle heavy guest traffic, and outdoor improvements — including custom metal railings on lanais and balconies — that stand up to the direct ocean exposure of front-row properties.</p>

      <h2>Azeka &amp; Central Kihei</h2>
      <p>The central Kihei area, anchored by the Azeka shopping centers along Kihei Road, has a different character than the waterfront zone. This area has seen significant residential development over the past decade, with newer single-family homes and small residential subdivisions extending inland from the commercial corridor. We've done kitchen and bathroom remodels, interior framing work, and general contracting projects throughout this zone, serving Kihei residents who want quality contractor work without mainland pricing expectations.</p>

      <h2>North Kihei &amp; Maui Meadows</h2>
      <p>North Kihei and the Maui Meadows subdivision above and around it represent a different residential profile — single-family homes on larger lots, many with mountain and ocean views, occupied by full-time Maui residents rather than vacation rental investors. Renovation work here tends to be whole-home remodels, room additions, and custom metal installations on decks and in yards. We do this work regularly and bring the same care to a Maui Meadows kitchen remodel as we do to a luxury resort renovation.</p>

      <h2>General Contracting Services in Kihei</h2>
      <p>Our full range of contractor services is available throughout Kihei:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>General contracting and project management</strong> — full scope management including Maui County permits, construction sequencing, trade coordination, and inspection sign-off for both residential and commercial projects in Kihei.</li>
        <li><strong>Kitchen remodels</strong> — from condo kitchen refreshes to full gut-and-rebuild renovations in Kihei homes. Cabinet removal and installation, drywall, flooring, custom carpentry, and finish work — all self-performed.</li>
        <li><strong>Bathroom renovations</strong> — full and partial bathroom remodels. Waterproofing, tile, custom shower work, vanity installation, and coordination with plumbing contractors for fixture work.</li>
        <li><strong>Interior framing and buildouts</strong> — wall modifications, room additions, layout reconfigurations, and commercial tenant improvement buildouts for Kihei businesses.</li>
        <li><strong>Custom metal fabrication</strong> — oceanfront-grade railings, gates, and architectural metalwork for Kihei properties. Material selection tailored to coastal exposure level.</li>
        <li><strong>Flooring and drywall</strong> — full flooring replacement and drywall work throughout Kihei properties, coordinated within the overall renovation scope.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Free On-Site Estimates in Kihei</h2>
      <p>We come to you anywhere in Kihei — South Kihei Road, Azeka, Maui Meadows, or any other neighborhood. Free on-site estimate, clear written scope, no obligation. Call (808) 795-4044 or submit a request online and we'll schedule a visit.</p>

      <h2>Kihei Contractor FAQ</h2>
      <p><strong>Do you work in my condo complex in Kihei?</strong> Yes. We work in condo complexes throughout Kihei and are familiar with HOA coordination requirements for renovation work. We'll work with your building management to get the proper approvals and coordinate the logistics of the project.</p>
      <p><strong>Can you work around my vacation rental schedule?</strong> We do this regularly for Kihei vacation rental owners. We'll schedule the project around your booking calendar to the extent possible, and we'll communicate clearly about timeline to help you manage your rental windows.</p>
      <p><strong>Do you handle Maui County permits for Kihei projects?</strong> Yes. Permit handling is included in our general contracting scope for projects that require permits.</p>
